<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-02-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-02-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="496" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                        <head>496. Telegram 1526 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d496fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/2–2156. Official Use Only.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-02-21">February 21, 1956,
                                    noon</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d496-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d496-1"/>
                        <p>1526. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Following list four names handed me by <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> 37th meeting February 18 (my telegram 1513,
                            paragraph 81):</p>
                        <p>[<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>]</p>
                        <pb facs="d496-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d496-2"/>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Note: Advance copy to Mr. Waddell (FE) 11 a.m. 2/21/CWO–JRL.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>